  "title": "Sales Engineer (Industrial Automation Products)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Build a strong understanding of the company’s products and applications through training sessions, seminars, and on-the-job learning.</li>\n  <li>Provide technical consultation and support to customers, recommending suitable products and services to meet application needs across various industries.</li>\n  <li>Adapt quickly to changing expectations and address challenges presented by customers.</li>\n  <li>Respond to customer requests promptly and efficiently.</li>\n  <li>Consistently secure new customers and maintain effective relationships.</li>\n  <li>Visit customer sites approximately three days per week to promote and sell products and services across a wide range of manufacturing and related sectors.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate on account strategies and contribute to the territory’s overall strategic plan.</li>\n  <li>Implement strategies for new product launches successfully.</li>\n  <li>Achieve growth in market share within the assigned sales territory.</li>\n  <li>Organize and coordinate off-site seminars and trade shows when required.</li>\n  <li>Manage daily activities independently with minimal supervision.</li>\n  <li>Adhere to company and departmental policies and procedures.</li>\n  <li>Perform other duties or projects as assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>\n<p><br></p>",
